article.headline: Arkansas State 74, Mississippi 69
article.story: OXFORD, Miss. (AP) -- J.J. Montgomery scored 24 points and Arkansas State hit 10 free throws in the final three minutes to beat Mississippi 74-69 on Friday. Tevoris Thompson had 17 points and Dewarick Spencer had 10 as the Indians (1-0) snapped the Ole Miss home court winning streak against non-conference teams at 12. The Rebels (0-1) had won 57 of their last 59 home games against non-conference opponents and had not lost a home opener since 1995 against Davidson. "We took a giant step forward beating a program of this caliber," said Arkansas State coach Dickey Nutt. "Ole Miss is going to be really good, it's just I thought we played really good for 40 minutes." The Indians, who led by as many as 15 points in the first half, had a 65-64 lead with 2:42 left before reeling off their string of free throws. Arkansas State was 10-for-14 from the free throw line. The Rebels never got closer than four points in the final minute. "Arkansas State did a good job of controlling the game," Ole Miss coach Rod Barnes said. "They did it by getting on us early. It was a long road back that took a lot out of us and that showed down the stretch." Justin Reed led the Rebels with 25 points and nine rebounds, but the Rebels were just 25-for-61 from the field, including 7-for-27 from 3-point range. Aaron Harper added 11 points, but was only 2-for-11 from three-point range and Marvin Moore added 10. Arkansas State dominated the boards, outrebounding the Rebels 40-31. Arkansas State had a 13-0 spurt midway through the first half to take a 17-8 lead. Thompson had eight straight points in the run, including a pair of three-point shots. The Indians led 40-30 at halftime after leading by as many as 15 points.
